\ls1\ilvl0
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Crossing the Hellespont\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \'93if you were to take account of everything\'85you would never do anything. It is better to have a brave heart and endure one half of the terrors we dread than to calculate all of the terrors and suffer nothing at all\'85big things are won by big danger.\'94 \'97 Xerxes\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Hedgehogs\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 relate everything to a single central vision through which all they say and do has significance\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Foxes\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 pursue many ends, often unrelated and even contradictory, connected, if at all, only\'a0in\'a0some de facto way\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 two ways to become intellectually indelible (unable to be forgotten):\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 be Delphic (ambiguous)\
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 be Aesopian (don\'92t cope with reality) use metaphors heavily\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 commanders must distinguish where they can act from what they must accept, trusting only\'a0in\'a0such craft as circumstances allow. Xerxes,\'a0in\'a0contrast, reshapes environments.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 The shortsighted Artabanus sees so much\'a0on\'a0the immediate horizon that complexity itself is the enemy. The farsighted Xerxes sees only a distant horizon\'a0on\'a0which ambitions are opportunities.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 how experts thought \'97 their style of reasoning \'97 did matter\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 foxes were far more proficient predictors than hedgehogs\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 foxes relied, for their predictions,\'a0on\'a0an intuitive \'91stitching together of diverse sources of information,\'92 but they tended to be too discursive \'97 too inclined to qualify their claims to hold and audience.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 hedgehogs shunned self-depreciation and brushed aside criticism. Aggressively deploying big explanations.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Xerxes failed, as is the habit of hedgehogs, to establish a proper relationship between his ends and his means\'85because ends only exist\'a0in\'a0one\'92s imagination. Means though, are stubbornly finite. Ends and means have to connect if anything is to happen. They\'92re never, however, interchangeable.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 little things can add up\'a0in\'a0unpredictably big ways \'97 and yet, leaders can\'92t let uncertainties paralyze them. They must appear to know what they are doing, even when they don\'92t.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf2 F. Scott Fitzgerald\'92s test for first-rate intelligence:\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf2 \'93the ability to hold two opposed ideas\'a0in\'a0the mind at the same time, and still retain the ability to function\'94\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Some people are neither hedgehogs nor foxes, some are both\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \'93\'85for what choices would we have if stuck within categories, mimicking animals, that mandated predictability\'85intelligence requires opposites, if freedom is choosing, then priorities can\'92t be predetermined.\'a0\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 we need to combine the hedgehog\'92s sense of direction and the fox\'92s sensitivity to surroundings\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 reconstituting the past as histories, biographies, poems, plays, novels or films\'85the best of these sharpen and shade simultaneously\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 choice always has characteristics of being inevitable and unpredictable\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 and infinite number of possibilities exist at an indeterminate number of cells, all simultaneously\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf2 Abe Lincoln has an\'a0ecological sensitivity that equally respects time, space and scale\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf2 short term sensitivity to surroundings with a long term sense of direction\cf0 \'a0(\'91fast\'92 and \'91slow\'92 thinking)\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 ends can be infinite, but means can never be\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 It is wrong to say that states have\'a0grand\'a0strategies, but people don\'92t. Alignments are necessary across time, space and scale\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Lincoln and Shakespeare had a lifetime to become who they were. Young people today don\'92t, because society segregates education, worsening the necessary \'91intellectual capital\'92 needed for leaders to be good at what they do when they arrive to the top.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 A plan, informed by the past, linked to the present, for achieving some goal\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 There are known unknowns, and unknown unknowns; friction is created at the collision of theory with reality\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf2 Lincoln knew where is compass was heading, whatever the unknowns that lied between him and his destination, he had\'a0in\'a0mind a range of options for dealing with these, based\'a0on\'a0hard-won lessons from this who have gone before, the rest was up to him\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 training is the best protection we have against\'a0strategies\'a0getting stupider as they become grander, a recurring problem\'a0in\'a0peace as well as\'a0in\'a0war.\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 to teach common sense\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 teach the basics, build stamina, enforce discipline, encourage collaboration, show you how to fail and to recover from failure.\'a0\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 leaders who have reached the top can become prisoners of their own preeminence, they lock themselves into roles from which they cannot escape\
\ls1\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 grand\'a0strategies\'a0\'97 alignments of means with ends
\f1\b0 \'a0\'97 become possible when leadership and common sense have frequent crossing between them\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Long Walls\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Unlike the Persians, the Greeks knew only scarcity, therefore they differed\'a0in\'a0all respects, accepting scarcity required specialization\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \'93knowledge of the past as an aid to understanding of the future, which\'a0in\'a0the course of human things must resemble if it does not reflect it.\'94\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 the past we can know only from imperfect sources, the future, we can\'92t know, other than that it will originate\'a0in\'a0the past, but then depart from it\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf2 Small causes can have big negative consequences, but progress forward takes place warily\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Peloponnesian War \'97 the unintended result of constructing a culture to support a\'a0strategy\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f0\b\fs26 need to create a culture focused\'a0on\'a0a cohesive\'a0grand\'a0strategy
\f1\b0 \
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Athens\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 the assembly functioned by divorcing virtue from status. If a man wished to participate \'97 a virtue \'97 then the \'91obscurity of his condition \'97 status \'97 wouldn\'92t prevent his doing so\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 The greeks thought of culture as character. The behavior of a city, state, or a people in small things, big things, and those in between\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Pericles was not Xerxes. \'93I am more afraid of our own blunders than of the enemy\'92s devices\'94\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Fear inspired by the growth of the Athenian power caused the Peloponnesian War\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Pericles was first steered with flows \'97 a strategy of persuasion\'85but persuasion, pursued with patience, would have come closer to cultivation\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf2 Building walls and proclaiming perimeters can be rational choices, for it makes little sense to pursue lost causes with limited resources. But strategy isn\'92t always a rational enterprise.\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 The abstractions of strategy and the emotions of strategists can never be separated: they can only be balanced\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 If credibility is always in doubt, then capabilities must become infinite or bluffs must become routine. Neither approach is sustainable: thats why walls exist in the first place. They buffer what\'92s important from what\'92s not\
\ls2\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Admiral Stansfield Turner\'85a man with flexible views on credentials but firm ones on the relevance of the classics of contemporary affairs\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0
\cf0 \
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Teachers and Tethers\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf2 Sun Tzu, sets forth principles, selected for validity across time and space, and then connects them to practices, bound by time and space. The Art of War is neither history nor biography, but a compilation of precepts, procedures and categorical claims.\cf0 \
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \'93The fish which covets bait is caught; troops who covet bait are defeated\'94\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf2 \'93They will understand the futility of shoveling shit uphill\'94\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Master Sun reflects but then acts, deploying maximum leverage against minimal resistance. Success comes as quickly as the least expenditure of resources and lives allow.\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \'93simplicity coexists with complexity and can guide us through it\'94\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Musical notes are only five in number, but their melodies are so numerous that one cannot hear them all.\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 No one can anticipate everything that might happen. Sensing possibilities, though, is better than having no sense at all of what to expect.\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Seek common sense by tethering a few principles to many practices. If tethered to principles, we need not be paralyzed. We learn to tether by having great teachers.\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Know the difference between inheriting a title and mastering the art of command. The first can happen overnight, the second can take a lifetime.\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Octavian remained focused on not winding up in a bloody heap on the senate floor, that required self-assessment\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 From a position of strength, Octavian worried about his weaknesses\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \'93To remove a rival was to remove a potential ally\'94\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Octavian arrived, viewed the body, asked the men to behave better in the future, and proceeded to hand out allocations. His calm so shamed the former troops that they demanded the murders\'92 punishment\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Octavian had a sense to delegate his authority, not to try to exercise it where he doubted his own competence\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Octavian was thinking ahead; how one decision can be made to affect what happens next\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf2 Octavian never tried to forge, form contingent events, causal chains\'85instead he seized opportunities while retaining objectives, he saw next steps\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Octavian rarely confused aspirations with capabilities, and he was always more careful, deploying strengths and in compensating for weaknesses\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \'93Offer an enemy a bait to lure him; feign disorder and strike hime\'85When he concentrates, prepare against him; where he is strong, avoid him\'85pretend inferiority and encourage his arrogance\'85keep him under a strain and wear him down.\'94\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf2 \'93Victories must connect, otherwise they lead no where\'94\
\ls3\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf2 \'93Plants aren\'92t aware that they are being made to mature in a certain way, but if firmly rooted and carefully tended they\'92ll cooperate.\'94\cf0 \
