\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 The Grandest Strategists\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 The novice cannot pass through these layers of increasing intensity of danger without sensing that here ideas are governed by other factors, that\cf4  the light of reason is refracted in a manner quite different from that which is normal in academic speculation.\cf0 \
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Clausewitz\'92s novice discovers that combat defies common sense,. In time though, logic surrounds, confounds, and supersedes such grammar. Heroics drain you. Offensives slow as supply lines lengthen. Dogs that catch cars never know what to do with them. \
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf4 Common sense is indeed like oxygen: the higher you go, the thinner it gets. As each triumph topped its antecedent, Napoleon\'92s grammar became less logic. Like Caesar, he rose so far above fundamentals as to lose sight of them altogether. Such ascents can be awe-inspiring: so too, in their day, were hot air balloons. But gravity is always present.\cf0 \
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Given the diversity of the real world, the application of principle rather than low allows for a grater latitude of judgment. Tolstoy, seeks at such length to subvert all laws.\
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 War is an act of force to compel our enemy to do our will\
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 The maximum use of force is in no way incompatible with the simultaneous use of intellect\
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Where two ideas form a true logical antithesis\'85then fundamentally, each is implied in the other\
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 ecological sensibility \'97 the man responsible for evaluating the whole must bring to the task the quality of intuition that perceives the truth at every point. Otherwise chaos of opinions would arise, and fatally entangle judgement\
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf4 Planning can only anticipate surprises by living with contradictions\
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 As each man\'92s strength\'85no longer responds to his will, the inertia of the whole gradually comes to rest on the commander\'92s will alone. The ardor of his spirit must rekindle the flame of purpose in all others; his inward fire must revive their hope.\
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Xerxes and Napoleon each went wrong in that they failed to perceive \'93truth at every point,\'94 which in these instances meant landscapes, logistics, climates, the morale of their troops and the strategies of their enemies.\
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 The good general must know friction in order to overcome it whenever possible, and in order not to expect a standard of achievement in his operations which this very friction makes impossible.\
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Beware of the rarity of common sense at high altitude\
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Kutuzov, he knows, will never invent anything, but he\'92ll listen to everything, remember everything, put everything in its place, won\'92t hinder anything useful or allow anything harmful. He understands that there is something stronger and more significant than his will \'97 the inevitable course of events \'97 and he\'92s able to see them, able to understand their significance, and, in view of that significance, is able to renounce\'85his personal will, and direct it elsewhere. He keeps his head out of his own clouds.\
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Leaders must keep their feet on the ground, whenever the thread became too thin I have preferred to break it off\'85just as some plants only bear fruit if they don\'92t shoot up too high\
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Those who never rise above anecdote \'97 those indefatigable repeaters of pointless stories \'97 are usually useless, for they \'93would construct all history of individual cases..digging only as deep as suits them, never getting down to the general factors that govern the matter.\
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf4 Theory becomes an excuse through which \'93limited and ignorant minds\'85justify their congenital incompetence. Clausewitz especially despises the \'93jargon, techicalities, and metaphors\'94 that swarm at high altitudes, a \'93lawless rabble of camp followers torn from context and enlisted as principles. \'93The light of day usually reveals them as mere trash,\'94 making theory \'93the very opposite of practice, and not infrequently the laughing stock of men whose military competence is beyond dispute.\'94\cf0 \
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Paradoxical trinity:\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 passions that cause combatants to lose their lives\
\ls7\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 skill of their commanders\
\ls7\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 coherence of their political objectives for which the war is being fought\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf4 Each situation requires a balancing derived from judgement and arising from experience, skills acquired by learning from the past and training for the future\
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf4 Theory serves practice and when practice corrects theory \'97 when it removes theorists\'92 horse blinders \'97 it returns the favor, preventing stumbles off cliffs, into swamps, and toward Moscow\cf0 \
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Modern term for stretching in strategy is \'93net assessment\'94\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 knowns\
\ls7\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 probabilities\
\ls7\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 unknowns\
