\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 The Greatest President\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 When asked to specify his education, Abe Lincoln wrote a single word, \'93defective\'94\
\ls8\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Lincoln perfected performance: no one used humor more readily, more aptly, or with less recycling. His anecdotes, often scatological, flowed as easily as the paper the shaky banks of his day issued as currency, but the stories never lacked point or purpose: it was said of Lincoln that he could \'93make a cat laugh.\'94 Behind the mask though was an enduring fatalism, as if something or someone else \'97 probably not God \'97 were directing him.\
\ls8\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf4 He educated himself, he read voraciously, remembered pragmatically, and applied lessons ingeniously.\
\ls8\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf4 Lincoln embraced a cause, acquired a compass and set a course \cf0 \
\ls8\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Lincoln started his speeches slowly, appearing at first to search for thoughts, words, even the more distant parts of his own anatomy. But as he warmed up, his gestures became purposeful, his voice began to carry, and his arguments laid lethal traps\'85with a relentless geometrical logic.\
\ls8\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \cf4 Lincoln drew strengths from contradictions, maybe because he contained so many. \cf0 They gave him amplitude \'97 physically, intellectually, morally \'97 absent in his rival\
\ls8\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \'93If we could first know where we are, and whither we are tending, we could then better judge what to do, and how to do it\'94\
\ls8\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Lincoln\'92s moral standard didn\'92t arise from faith, or formal ethics, or even the law, a profession necessarily pragmatic in its pursuit of justice. It emerged instead from what experience had taught, from the self education that widened it, and from the logic in which Lincoln grounded his oratorical lightning. Judge Douglas\'92s amorality, therefore, was not just wrong: it violated the most basic requirements of common sense.\
\ls8\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 As far as I know, Lincoln never read Augustine or Machiavelli on the competing demands of souls and states. Yet few who came after them more skillfully navigated the polarity.\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 \'93he wanted God on his side, but he must have Kentucky\'94\
\ls8\ilvl2
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 means can never be considered in isolation of purpose\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 \cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 Lincoln critically assessed costs, neither brushing them aside, nor dreading them to the point of immobility\
\ls8\ilvl1
\f2\fs20 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}
\f1\fs26 No one more artfully stuck to non-negotiables while selectively stating them\
\pard\pardeftab560\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl2
